In this work, we use the Multi-dimensional Damped Exponential Moving Average (MD-EMA) proposed by MEGA [37] for the kernel parameterization, whose details are included in Section A.3. Note that our work is orthogonal to the SSM kernel design as long as it can provide an efficient computation of the recurrent state representation. It is possible that using a more advanced SSM such as Liquid-S4 [23] or S5 [50] can lead to better performance, but we keep using MD-EMA for a fair comparison with MEGA. Given the state representation , a latent configurator with one linear layer is applied to obtain the decision vector and the confidence probability vector with the Tempered Softmax, i.e.,

